videos.description: Clinton Lynch takes the toss sweep in to the second level for a nice run, setting up Georgia Tech in the red zone.
videos.headline: Lynch gashes Miami for 48-yard run

videos.description: J.J. Green dives by the pylon to score for a Georgia Tech touchdown.
videos.headline: Green gets the edge and dives in for TD

videos.description: TaQuon Marshall somehow avoids the sack and uses a jump pass to find a wide open J.J. Green for the score.
videos.headline: Marshall escapes the sack and tosses to Green for TD

videos.description: Travis Homer uses some tough running and speed for a 32-yard gain.
videos.headline: Homer takes off for big run

videos.description: Georgia Tech played well but coach Paul Johnson thinks they left some opportunities on the field in the first half.
videos.headline: Johnson wants his offense to execute better in 2nd half

videos.description: Malik Rosier finds Travis Homer who does the rest for an athletic 17-yard TD.
videos.headline: Rosier tosses it to Homer who dives in for TD

videos.description: Miami tries an onside kick to start the second half, and Lamont Simmons takes it all the way for a Georgia Tech touchdown.
videos.headline: Georgia Tech returns onside kick to the house

videos.description: TaQuon Marshall takes a rare deep shot to a wide open Ricky Jeune to put Georgia Tech in the red zone.
videos.headline: Marshall throws a bomb to Jeune for 48 yards

videos.description: Malik Rosier finds Jeff Thomas for a huge pass that sets Miami up in the red zone.
videos.headline: Rosier slings it to Thomas for 70-yard gain

videos.description: Travis Homer makes a man miss and finds his way in to the end zone for a Miami touchdown.
videos.headline: Homer takes off for a 27-yard TD

videos.description: Darrell Langham catches a crazy pass off a tip and in double coverage to keep Miami's hopes alive on 4th down.
videos.headline: Langham comes up with incredible catch on 4th down

videos.description: Michael Badgley drilled a chip shot to complete the improbable comeback win for Miami.
videos.headline: Badgley nails game-winning 24-yard field goal

videos.description: Georgia Tech used five laterals on desperation kickoff before finally getting tackled. Miami fights back to win it 25-24.
videos.headline: Georgia Tech dramatic final play of the game

videos.description: Head Coach Mark Richt thought his quarterback threw a bad pass on 4th down but it didn't matter because Darrell Langham caught it anyway.
videos.headline: Richt on another crazy comeback win for the Canes

videos.description: Miami's  wild fourth quarter drive and 4th down conversion led to another close win as the Hurricanes remain unbeaten.
videos.headline: Georgia Tech dominated until the rain came down and then the Canes came back
